4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp that allows individuals to become cybersecurity specialists without any prior knowledge. The program focuses on providing a strong foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills for securing these environments. Participants will also learn about cloud security, penetration testing (offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The bootcamp covers topics such as data loss prevention (DLP) strategies and compliance with international standards like ISO 27001 and NIST. The program lasts for 16 weeks and includes three live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. After completing the bootcamp, participants will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate, recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required to enroll in the program. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit their website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop